To evaluate the influence of relapses in quality of life
of patients with relapsing remitting multiple sclerosis.
Forty-nine MS patients with a relapse included in a Phase
IV, multicenter, randomized, double blind trial that showed the no
inferiority of oMP compared to ivMP to treat MS relapses, were ana-
lysed. The protocol variables were baseline disability (measured by
EDSS), relapse severity (increasing of EDSS = or >1.0) and quality
of life (measured by MusiQol at the time of the relapse (t=0) and at
week 1 and 4 after MP treatment). The primary outcome was to ana-
lysed MusiQol at t=0, week 1 and week 4 after high-dose MP treat-
ment. Secondary outcomes were to analysed the relationship
between MusiQol with relapse severity and previous disability.
